Not sure exactly why I decided to post, was kinda bored heh. Been seeing a lot of high horse posts lately with no logic to them, guess I finally reached my limit. *sigh* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/utatianaefatecaster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tatianae Fatecaster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 341<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/01 8:37:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ....</span><hr size=1> I've said all I'm really going to say about it...accosting him here to defend isn't the right place. Does everyone need to stand up before a public jury? If so then everyone compile your list of who wronged you and how and make sure you come in and &quot;force&quot; them in to defense irregardless if it is a misunderstanding. The Frizzy event was a *classic* example that misunderstandings do happen and you have no clue sometimes what is happening on the other side of the keyboard. <br>
